---
description: When adding or renaming vox CLI commands, keep registry and docs in sync.
globs: crates/vox-cli/**/*.rs, contracts/cli/*.yaml, contracts/cli/*.json, contracts/operations/*.yaml, contracts/operations/*.json, docs/src/reference/cli.md, docs/src/architecture/cli-*.md, docs/src/ci/command-*.md
alwaysApply: false
---

# CLI command changes

- Add the **`vox-cli` projection** to **`contracts/operations/catalog.v1.yaml`** (schema **`catalog.v1.schema.json`**), then run **`vox ci operations-sync --target cli --write`** (or **`--target all`**) so **`contracts/cli/command-registry.yaml`** is regenerated (respect **`command-registry.schema.json`** on the committed artifact).
- Update **`docs/src/reference/cli.md`** for any `vox-cli` row with default **`ref_cli_required`** (omit `ref_cli_required: false` only when intentionally exempt).
- For new **top-level** subcommands, add a row to **`docs/src/architecture/cli-reachability-ssot.md`** unless the registry sets **`reachability_required: false`**.
- Run **`vox ci operations-verify`** and **`cargo run -p vox-cli -- ci command-compliance`** from the repo root before merging.
- See **`docs/src/architecture/cli-design-rules-ssot.md`** and **`docs/src/ci/command-compliance-ssot.md`**.
